post_text: We have been made aware that a neighboring school district is reporting a scam that involves families receiving phone calls from someone claiming they are from the school and that they will be coming to their home to retrieve their Chromebook. Although we have not received any reports of this happening in our school district, please be aware that we rarely send district employees to a student's home. If you would receive a call such as this or someone would visit your home claiming to be a district employee, please notify local law enforcement. #WilsonSD

post_text: At our recent School Board Meeting, we welcomed our new Student Representative, Giani Clarke. Giani is the Student Government President for the 2020-2021 school year. Congrats to the cast of Beauty and the Beast on a fantastic performance! We are excited to share this amazing musical with our community where it will be live-streamed to an audience of cars in the Wilson High School parking lot on Thursday, July 16 at 8:30 pm (parking lots open at 8:00 pm).

We STILL have a limited number of spots that are open to the community for this event. To reserve your spot on a first-come, first-served basis, please fill out the Drive-In Car Reservation Form, accessible at www.wilsontheaterco.org. If you are not able to attend the drive-in event, the show will also be available via this link https://youtu.be/fvwObPwV2Nk. Please note that the rain date for this event is Saturday, July 18.

post_text:
Congratulations to the team of Cole Chmielewski, Sanchita Bhusari, McCord Peterson, Luke Kline, and Colby Snyder for winning the Pennsylvania Governor's STEM Competition and for being named Grand Champions!

In February, our team won the Berks County competition at the BCIU (pictured below) with their project that tracks the amount of carbon emissions saved by riding a bicycle instead of driving a car. The statewide competition was held virtually this year with 28 teams from across the state competing in the contest.

We are Bulldog Proud of you! #WilsonSD

post_text: Here is a behind-the-scenes look at our District social media team from the past school year. Our Communications Department interns, Rachel and Reagan, did an amazing job sharing many of our posts as part of their honors internship experience-- Motivational Monday, Throwback Thursday, Focus of the Faculty Friday, all our Senior Spotlights and so much more! These talented students worked so hard to share the stories of the Wilson School District with our community! Congratulations on your graduation-- you will be missed! #WilsonSD

post_text:
It's National School Counseling Week! This week is set aside to highlight the unique contribution of school counselors and the tremendous impact they can have in helping students achieve school success and plan for a career.

At Wilson, our school counselors are actively engaged in helping students examine their abilities, strengths, interests and talents; work in partnership with parents as they encounter the challenges of raising children in today’s world; focusing on positive ways to enhance students’ academic, post secondary and social/emotional development; and work with teachers and other educators to provide an educational system where students can realize their potential and set healthy, realistic and optimistic aspirations for themselves.

For all of their contributions to the lives of our students, we’d like to honor and acknowledge our fantastic team of school counselors! #WilsonSD #WilsonEmpowered

post_text: We were thrilled to celebrate Braille Literacy Month this week at Wilson! Our staff participated in "Blue Jeans for Braille" to raise money for the first-ever Pennsylvania Braille Challenge. And our students who use braille celebrated by leading various activities throughout the district to raise awareness among their classmates. What an amazing opportunity! #WilsonSD

ATHLETIC UPDATE! Due to the pending weather forecast, there are some changes to this weekend's athletic schedule. Please check them out!

-Middle School Wrestling travelling to Cocalico has been cancelled

-HS Wrestling travelling to Cocalico has been postponed to Monday, 1/20 @ 4:30PM

-Indoor Track travelling to the New Balance Games in New York City has been cancelled

-Freshmen Boys Basketball hosting William Penn has been postponed to Saturday, 2/1 @ 9:30AM @ Wilson West Middle School

-HS Boys Basketball travelling to Downingtown East has been postponed to Wednesday, 1/22 @ 5:30PM (JV first)

-HS Girls Basketball hosting Downingtown East has been postponed to Tuesday, 1/21 @ 6:00PM (JV first)
